text: Haralson County, Georgia is a county in the state of Georgia. Its county seat is Buchanan. As of 2020, 29,919 people were living in the county. == Cities and towns == *Bremen *Buchanan *Tallapoosa *Waco *Budapest *Felton == References == Category:1856 establishments in Georgia (U.S. state) Category:Georgia (U.S. state) counties
